<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,722,821]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The genus has frequently been placed in a family of its own, 
<taxonomicName box="[827,975,722,748]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperinidae</taxonomicName>
(e.g., Krivosheina 1997, 
<bibRefCitation author="Skartveit, J." box="[1256,1424,722,749]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="3 - 42" refId="ref51329" refString="Skartveit, J. (2009) Fossil Hesperinidae and Bibionidae (Diptera: Bibionoidea) from Baltic amber. Studia dipterologica, 15, 3 - 42." type="journal article" year="2009">Skartveit 2009</bibRefCitation>
), however, recent, molecular studies (Sevƒçic 
<emphasis box="[649,708,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2016) suggest it is relatively closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[1259,1377,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1259,1377,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus has previously been found from the Oligocene of 
<collectingCountry box="[780,856,795,821]" name="France" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, A. &amp; Skartveit, J." box="[871,1125,794,821]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="85 - 89" refId="ref51169" refString="Nel, A. &amp; Skartveit, J. (2012): Occurrence of the genus Hesperinus Walker (Diptera, Hesperinidae) in the Oligocene of France. Studia dipterologica, 18, 85 - 89." type="journal article" year="2012">Nel &amp; Skartveit, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
